1
00:01:08,708 --> 00:01:09,500
Actually,

2
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:15,375
I am Chen Jing'an.

3
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:19,291
She says she's Chen Jing'an.

4
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:21,375
Zhu Niannian,

5
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,083
today isn't April Fool's Day.

6
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:26,166
Don't laugh.

7
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:28,291
I'm being very serious with you.

8
00:01:28,791 --> 00:01:30,291
I really am Chen Jing'an.

9
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:33,333
Did you and Chen Jing'an

10
00:01:34,166 --> 00:01:36,000
lose at Truth or Dare?

11
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,416
Think about it carefully.

12
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:43,666
Do you think the current Chen Jing'an

13
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:45,041
is the same as the old Chen Jing'an?

14
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:46,875
Do you remember last time

15
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:49,500
when Li Minqiu hit her on the head with a basketball?

16
00:01:49,833 --> 00:01:50,416
Would something like that

17
00:01:50,416 --> 00:01:52,291
ever happen to me, Chen Jing'an?

18
00:01:54,041 --> 00:01:54,750
The two of us

19
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:56,750
swapped places.

20
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:04,791
You two really made up a complete story.

21
00:02:08,207 --> 00:02:09,875
Are you forcing me to use my ultimate move?

22
00:02:14,416 --> 00:02:15,875
When you were in eighth grade,

23
00:02:16,791 --> 00:02:18,041
You had a fight with your mom and ran away from home.

24
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,500
You even took your family’s bicycle.

25
00:02:19,916 --> 00:02:20,582
And then?

26
00:02:20,582 --> 00:02:22,250
You broke your leg halfway there.

27
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:23,041
You ended up in the hospital.

28
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,332
When I went to visit you at the hospital,

29
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:26,875
you were sobbing your heart out,

30
00:02:26,875 --> 00:02:27,457
crying as you told me

31
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,791
that your mom didn’t understand you.

32
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,832
You even hugged me while crying,

33
00:02:30,875 --> 00:02:31,500
saying

34
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:33,041
I must never tell anyone about your embarrassing moment.

35
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:35,082
Would I ever lie to you

36
00:02:35,166 --> 00:02:36,291
and tell others about this?

37
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:37,625
I swore a solemn oath.

38
00:02:37,832 --> 00:02:38,416
Wait a second.

39
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,332
Wait.

40
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:40,541
Wait, wait, wait.

41
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:41,250
Hold on.

42
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:43,000
Let me catch my breath.

43
00:02:44,125 --> 00:02:44,916
Let me catch my breath first.

44
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:47,916
Let me catch my breath first.

45
00:03:00,832 --> 00:03:01,291
Hurry up and write.

46
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:01,916
Let me copy it when you're done.

47
00:03:02,957 --> 00:03:04,041
I don't know how to write it.

48
00:03:04,707 --> 00:03:05,332
Go.

49
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:06,541
We're not afraid of him.

50
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,166
You'll definitely beat him this time too.

51
00:03:09,832 --> 00:03:11,250
What's going on between you and Zhu Niannian?

52
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:13,291
You've really been acting more and more like her lately.

53
00:03:14,957 --> 00:03:15,416
Don't touch my hair.

54
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:16,457
Come with me to the bathroom.

55
00:03:18,457 --> 00:03:19,541
I just transferred here.

56
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:20,791
I thought you were Deng Shasha.

57
00:03:20,957 --> 00:03:21,416
Sorry.

58
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:22,625
You won't snitch to the teacher, will you?

59
00:03:24,582 --> 00:03:25,666
How did you end up acting just like...

60
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:27,416
...Chen Jing'an?

61
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,666
You really are...

62
00:03:33,666 --> 00:03:34,791
...Chen Jing'an turned into...

63
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,875
...Zhu Niannian.

64
00:03:39,666 --> 00:03:40,916
I'm not dreaming, am I?

65
00:03:43,666 --> 00:03:44,457
Does this hurt?

66
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:47,582
It hurts.

67
00:03:49,207 --> 00:03:50,207
So what's really going on?

68
00:03:50,332 --> 00:03:51,207
Keep your voice down.

69
00:03:53,332 --> 00:03:54,125
You guys didn't...

70
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:56,041
...go through some supernatural event, did you?

71
00:03:56,332 --> 00:03:57,125
Don't talk nonsense.

72
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:00,000
There must be...

73
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,582
...some scientific explanation for this.

74
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:03,750
We just haven't figured out the reason yet.

75
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:04,625
About this...

76
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:05,750
I'm only telling you.

77
00:04:06,207 --> 00:04:07,207
Only the three of us know.

78
00:04:07,832 --> 00:04:08,791
You can't tell anyone.

79
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:11,207
I'm only telling you because we're close.

80
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:14,082
Don't worry.

81
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,875
I'd never betray my buddies, not even if you beat me to death.

82
00:04:18,665 --> 00:04:19,750
Good brother.

83
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:29,540
Good morning, everyone.

84
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,250
Embrace the spring breeze and raise your ambitions.

85
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:33,415
Celebrate our glorious years.

86
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:34,790
We are about to welcome

87
00:04:34,790 --> 00:04:37,040
the 60th anniversary of Nancheng No. 2 High School.

88
00:04:37,290 --> 00:04:39,375
The city TV station will send a crew to film.

89
00:04:39,790 --> 00:04:42,040
To showcase the spirit of our students,

90
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:43,000
the school

91
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:46,000
will organize a host selection event for the anniversary.

92
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:48,415
Interested students can

93
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:50,415
go to the student council office

94
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:51,708
to sign up before Wednesday.

95
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:53,790
The TV station is coming to record.

96
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,250
Doesn't that mean we can be on TV?

97
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,040
Yeah.

98
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,040
If you become the host,

99
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,875
your parents can see you on TV at home.

100
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,583
Forget about hosting.

101
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:02,958
You have to be good-looking and eloquent to get chosen.

102
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:03,875
I think this time

103
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:05,250
it'll probably be Zhu Niannian.

104
00:05:05,415 --> 00:05:06,125
As for her,

105
00:05:06,665 --> 00:05:08,083
she's just good-looking.

106
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:09,290
When it comes to eloquence,

107
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:10,915
the winner of the last speech contest

108
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:12,540
wasn't it Liu Xinyi?

109
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:13,458
Exactly.

110
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,290
I think it's her.

111
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,000
I think so too.

112
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,125
No, I think it's her.

113
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:32,290
She's just good-looking.

114
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:41,083
Stop sighing.

115
00:05:41,083 --> 00:05:41,665
After all, you are

116
00:05:41,665 --> 00:05:43,540
one of the most famous beautiful teachers at school.

117
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:45,750
What's wrong with asking you to perform on stage?

118
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,625
They're all students.

119
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:49,165
How could I possibly do that?

120
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,375
Besides, I'm a history teacher.

121
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,750
I don't have any special talents.

122
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:56,333
Do you want me to

123
00:05:56,958 --> 00:05:58,290
go up there and perform

124
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,250
by reciting the Records of the Grand Historian?

125
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:01,915
Stop laughing.

126
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:03,458
Hurry up and help me think of something.

127
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:06,250
How about

128
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:06,790
you go on stage

129
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,540
and do a Hanfu fashion show?

130
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,040
A Hanfu fashion show?

131
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,790
That's even more embarrassing.

132
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,083
What's so embarrassing about that?

133
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,625
Just pretend you're giving a lecture.

134
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:16,833
Take a few steps and come down.

135
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,290
Excuse me.

136
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:20,790
Niannian.

137
00:06:21,208 --> 00:06:22,290
Are you here to see Teacher Shi?

138
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,083
I asked her to come.

139
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:24,875
Zhu Niannian,

140
00:06:25,165 --> 00:06:26,415
the school anniversary is coming up soon.

141
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:27,915
About the play "Romeo and Juliet,"

142
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,833
are you okay with it?

143
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,833
A play?

144
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,500
Why is there a play to perform too?

145
00:06:34,665 --> 00:06:36,665
Zhu Niannian never told me about this.

146
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:41,415
Tian Ye already knows

147
00:06:41,415 --> 00:06:42,500
about us switching places.

148
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:44,040
He promised he wouldn't tell anyone.

149
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:44,875
So don't worry.

150
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:47,665
And also,

151
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,583
I originally planned during the school anniversary

152
00:06:49,583 --> 00:06:50,290
to perform with Tian Ye

153
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,665
in their song and dance show.

154
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:53,665
But suddenly, Teacher Shi came to me

155
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:55,290
and asked me to act in some play.

156
00:06:55,583 --> 00:06:56,915
I didn't really know what was going on at the time,

157
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,083
so I didn't dare say anything.

158
00:06:58,625 --> 00:06:59,165
Well,

159
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,540
the play shouldn't be

160
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:01,540
a very important thing, right?

161
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:02,500
No,

162
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:03,625
this play

163
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:05,708
was something Teacher Shi asked me about

164
00:07:05,875 --> 00:07:07,333
during last semester's arts performance.

165
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:08,500
I agreed to do it.

166
00:07:09,415 --> 00:07:10,790
Actually, I'm not that interested

167
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:12,290
in acting in plays.

168
00:07:12,665 --> 00:07:13,415
It's just that

169
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,500
I couldn't refuse the teacher at the time.

170
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:16,750
That's good, then.

171
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:18,000
I thought

172
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,665
it was like the last speech contest,

173
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,040
where if I messed up, I'd be done for.

174
00:07:22,458 --> 00:07:23,333
Since that's the case,

175
00:07:23,415 --> 00:07:25,125
I'll just find a way to turn it down.

176
00:07:25,165 --> 00:07:25,875
But

177
00:07:26,165 --> 00:07:27,875
I've already promised Teacher Shi.

178
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:30,040
Wouldn't it be a bit bad to back out now?

179
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:32,125
It's not that important anyway.

180
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:33,083
Even if I don't act,

181
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,375
they'll just find someone else to do it.

182
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,500
It's fine, right?

183
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:36,375
Besides,

184
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:38,500
even though I'm pretending to be you,

185
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:39,915
I can't possibly

186
00:07:39,915 --> 00:07:40,625
do everything

187
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,125
exactly the way you would have.

188
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,290
As long as it doesn't cause any trouble,

189
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,040
I think

190
00:07:46,165 --> 00:07:47,665
I have the right to choose what to do

191
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:48,833
and what not to do.

192
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:49,790
You do too.

193
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:50,708
After all,

194
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:51,415
we don't know

195
00:07:51,415 --> 00:07:52,750
when we'll be able to switch back.

196
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,125
What do you think?

197
00:07:54,165 --> 00:07:55,875
I think what you said makes sense.

198
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:57,165
Actually,

199
00:07:57,290 --> 00:07:59,000
I'm also planning to use your identity

200
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,083
to enter the host selection competition.

201
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,665
Wouldn't everyone be scared to death?

202
00:08:03,665 --> 00:08:04,875
Chen Jing'an as the host—

203
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:32,041
Help!

204
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:33,833
How did I end up standing here?

205
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,541
What's that shining in the window?

206
00:08:44,958 --> 00:08:46,125
That's the east.

207
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:48,750
Juliet is the sun.

208
00:08:50,125 --> 00:08:51,083
Rise,

209
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,458
beautiful sun,

210
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:55,000
and drive away the jealous moon.

211
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:58,291
Does that guy down there have to be so dramatic?

212
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:06,791
Romeo, oh Romeo

213
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,500
Why must you be

214
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,208
Romeo

215
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:15,125
He’s not a foot

216
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:17,250
He’s not a hand

217
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:22,041
He’s not a nose or a face

218
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:23,333
What is he then

219
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,125
Juliet

220
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,250
You said the wrong line

221
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:27,291
I can’t remember

222
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:28,291
Say the next line

223
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:36,708
Then I’ll do as you say

224
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:39,708
As long as you call me for love again

225
00:09:40,041 --> 00:09:41,916
Then I’ll be baptized again

226
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,458
And renamed

227
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,250
From now on

228
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:48,041
I’ll no longer be called Romeo

229
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:54,500
What’s the next line

230
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,166
Who are you

231
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:02,750
You are

232
00:10:07,041 --> 00:10:08,083
From Inner Mongolia

233
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:10,250
Why are you standing here

234
00:10:10,708 --> 00:10:11,708
Romeo

235
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,125
Stop, stop, stop

236
00:10:15,583 --> 00:10:16,500
Zhu Nian Nian

237
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,500
Are you even memorizing your lines

238
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:20,208
Is that Inner Mongolia

239
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,000
That’s Montague

240
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:31,708
Teacher

241
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:34,333
I think this is too hard

242
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:35,958
I really can’t remember it

243
00:10:42,291 --> 00:10:43,916
Zhu Niannian, what are you doing?

244
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:45,125
You can't remember your lines.

245
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:46,541
And you ruined the props again.

246
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,041
Teacher.

247
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:50,708
I really can't remember them.

248
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:52,625
Niannian.

249
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:53,458
Ms. Shi.

250
00:10:53,458 --> 00:10:55,208
Didn't I tell you to memorize them a long time ago?

251
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:57,000
If you perform like this at the school anniversary,

252
00:10:57,041 --> 00:10:58,500
everyone will laugh at you.

253
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:00,250
Teacher.

254
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,416
No more excuses.

255
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:02,625
Let's leave it at that for now.

256
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,208
Go back and memorize them properly.

257
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,958
Next time we'll rehearse the whole thing.

258
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:08,291
Niannian.

259
00:11:08,708 --> 00:11:10,250
Memorize them well, I believe in you.

260
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:11,250
You can do it.

261
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,291
Teacher.

262
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:19,250
It's okay, senior.

263
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,708
I think you did really well just now.

264
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:22,833
I even felt

265
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:25,333
it was like a real Juliet standing there.

266
00:11:28,291 --> 00:11:29,000
Um...

267
00:11:29,208 --> 00:11:30,291
Senior Zhu Niannian.

268
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,625
Let me introduce myself.

269
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:33,875
I'm Wang Lihong from Class 1, Grade 10.

270
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:38,541
Can I add you on QQ?

271
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:44,500
What's wrong?

272
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:50,166
Chen Jing'an.

273
00:11:50,416 --> 00:11:51,916
I heard that when you were acting in the play,

274
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:53,208
Teacher Shi got angry.

275
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:55,541
It's nothing serious.

276
00:11:56,041 --> 00:11:57,375
I didn't want to act in the first place.

277
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,875
So I didn't even memorize the lines.

278
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,208
Chen Jing'an.

279
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:01,708
Why don't you just act properly?

280
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:03,083
Stop going against the teacher.

281
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,500
Acting in a play is much easier than taking an exam.

282
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:07,416
Just treat it as

283
00:12:07,583 --> 00:12:09,166
an after-class relaxation activity.

284
